<p>Is there a way to cancel a ES7 async function?</p>  <p>In this example, on click, I want to abort async function call before calling new.</p>  <pre class="lang-js prettyprint-override"><code>async function draw(){   for(;;){     drawRandomRectOnCanvas();     await sleep(100);   } }  function sleep(t){   return new Promise(cb=&gt;setTimeout(cb,t)); }  let asyncCall;  window.addEventListener('click', function(){   if(asyncCall)     asyncCall.abort(); // this dont works   clearCanvas();   asyncCall = draw(); }); </code></pre>